
[1]cesure

   CESURE, n. A pause in verse, so introduced as to aid the recital, and
   render the versification more melodious. It divides a verse or line
   into equal or unequal parts. Its most pleasing effect is produced, when
   it is placed at the end of the second foot, or in the middle, or at the
   end of the third foot.
